    supports HTML5 video This is a modal window. Beginning of dialog window. Escape will cancel and close the window. End of dialog window. “Sometimes people come with metals and say they were told by the owner that they could take them. This happened with the building that burned down, but it turns out they were lying. But in some cases they are telling the truth,” she said. Community Policing Forum (CPF) chairperson Tony da Canha said he reported the incident to the police yesterday. “The most frightening thing is that the building has been condemned. No one should be in there because it could collapse at any minute.” He said vagrants had stolen window and door frames without knowing how this would affect the building’s structure. The manager of Allparts Group in Durban, which owns the premises in New Germany, refused to comment. Daily News